WEBVTT

00:00:00.344 --> 00:00:01.954
(Child actors were accompanied by a guardian...)

00:00:02.014 --> 00:00:03.784
(and filmed in a safe, supervised environment.)

00:00:05.758 --> 00:00:07.288
This thistle rice is so fragrant and delicious.

00:00:07.658 --> 00:00:10.588
This braised pollack. Su Im's grandmother dropped it off.

00:00:11.958 --> 00:00:13.828
Nurse Oh, about the sign on the door...

00:00:14.128 --> 00:00:16.468
Did you put up a sign saying we're closed this afternoon?

00:00:16.468 --> 00:00:17.598
Yes, I did.

00:00:18.238 --> 00:00:19.838
Dad, where's the conference today?

00:00:19.998 --> 00:00:23.638
Yeouido. I'm just taking the subway.

00:00:24.778 --> 00:00:28.478
Dr. Yang also took the afternoon off to go to City Hall.

00:00:28.578 --> 00:00:32.478
Right. He went to the info session about revitalizing the market.

00:00:34.018 --> 00:00:36.748
He's in total work mode these days.

00:00:37.718 --> 00:00:39.618
It's good to see him working so hard.

00:00:40.388 --> 00:00:44.128
That reminds me. Did you hear about the clinic manager's husband?

00:00:44.188 --> 00:00:45.728
He's going to Saudi Arabia for work, apparently.

00:00:45.998 --> 00:00:49.028
- All of a sudden? - Yes. It was very last-minute.

00:00:49.428 --> 00:00:51.698
I think he was supposed to leave today.

00:00:52.168 --> 00:00:55.838
I wonder when Seong Mi will be done with her taping today.

00:00:55.908 --> 00:00:59.038
Right. She pulls all-nighters, filming for two straight days.

00:00:59.778 --> 00:01:04.548
I should have made her eat. She needs strength for the shoot.

00:01:04.718 --> 00:01:05.718
I know.

00:01:11.118 --> 00:01:14.118
You're dead! Only one of us is walking away from this.

00:01:14.118 --> 00:01:16.228
- Stop it! - I'll kill you both!

00:01:16.288 --> 00:01:18.758
- I'm going to kill you both today! - Stop it!

00:01:23.928 --> 00:01:25.538
My goodness! What do I do?

00:01:29.808 --> 00:01:32.238
Oh, no. What do I do?

00:01:32.338 --> 00:01:34.878
Hey!

00:01:42.418 --> 00:01:46.358
- Are you all right? - Mother, are you okay?

00:01:46.918 --> 00:01:49.628
Stepmom, are you crazy? Why did you hit her?

00:01:49.928 --> 00:01:52.128
- No, that's not what happened... - This is a disaster!

00:01:52.228 --> 00:01:55.298
- What should I do? - I'll take her to the hospital.

00:01:55.568 --> 00:01:56.828
- Seriously... - What...

00:02:00.068 --> 00:02:03.368
Father! Oh, no! My goodness.

00:02:04.708 --> 00:02:05.878
I'm off, Grandma.

00:02:05.938 --> 00:02:09.878
Okay. Don't study too hard. Make sure you eat well, okay?

00:02:09.948 --> 00:02:11.818
- Okay. - Please help us!

00:02:13.348 --> 00:02:16.348
My goodness, what is going on? What's wrong?

00:02:16.418 --> 00:02:17.418
Mom.

00:02:17.488 --> 00:02:19.458
- What is going on? What happened? - Oh, my gosh!

00:02:19.518 --> 00:02:20.718
- Honey! - Seong Mi!

00:02:20.788 --> 00:02:23.728
- I'm okay. - Let's get you inside, quick!

00:02:24.258 --> 00:02:26.098
- My goodness. - What... What happened?

00:02:26.098 --> 00:02:27.728
Was it an accident?

00:02:32.898 --> 00:02:36.438
Okay. Your pupils are symmetrical, and there's no bleeding.

00:02:36.668 --> 00:02:38.378
Are you seeing flashes of light? How do you feel?

00:02:38.978 --> 00:02:42.748
If you're seeing flashes, we must go to the ER for an exam.

00:02:42.808 --> 00:02:46.818
It hurts, but I don't have any other symptoms.

00:02:47.278 --> 00:02:48.688
Are you sure you're okay?

00:02:48.688 --> 00:02:51.688
Yes, my vision's blurry. I guess it's because of the shock.

00:02:52.288 --> 00:02:55.928
- I'm fine otherwise, really. - So it was an accident, Seong Mi?

00:02:56.088 --> 00:02:58.998
My goodness, what on earth happened?

00:03:01.158 --> 00:03:03.798
Why won't you say anything? This is so frustrating.

00:03:06.268 --> 00:03:09.238
- Well, it's just... - I'm so sorry.

00:03:10.868 --> 00:03:13.908
Dr. Han was hit by my stepmom.

00:03:14.648 --> 00:03:15.648
- What? - What?

00:03:16.278 --> 00:03:17.748
The thing is...

00:03:18.318 --> 00:03:21.418
My uncle and Woo Jae's aunt were having an affair,

00:03:21.488 --> 00:03:24.288
so my uncle... No, my aunt and Woo Jae's aunt...

00:03:24.348 --> 00:03:27.958
They were fighting, so my stepmom and Dr. Han tried to stop them...

00:03:28.858 --> 00:03:29.858
Hey.

00:03:30.928 --> 00:03:32.858
Who did you just say was involved?

00:03:38.398 --> 00:03:41.068
Wait a minute. Why isn't anyone else shocked?

00:03:41.638 --> 00:03:45.078
Am I the only one just hearing this? Did you all already know?

00:03:49.108 --> 00:03:50.248
You knew about this?

00:03:51.548 --> 00:03:52.548
No.

00:03:54.618 --> 00:03:55.848
Seong Mi.

00:04:07.658 --> 00:04:11.098
We had pork cutlets together, and now we're having some coffee,

00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:12.668
so I feel like I'm on top of the world.

00:04:14.968 --> 00:04:17.168
Are you really sure about this?

00:04:18.038 --> 00:04:20.838
Are you asking if I'm confident I can date you,

00:04:20.838 --> 00:04:22.308
even with our families as sworn enemies?

00:04:25.018 --> 00:04:26.648
Would I have confessed if I weren't?

00:04:27.518 --> 00:04:30.288
My gosh. It's not going to be easy.

00:04:31.918 --> 00:04:34.158
Don't keep me in suspense. Just tell me.

00:04:34.558 --> 00:04:35.558
Are we...

00:04:37.088 --> 00:04:39.028
official as of today?

00:04:45.868 --> 00:04:49.108
What terrible timing. Who is this?

00:04:50.638 --> 00:04:52.708
Let me just get this, then I'll give you my answer.

00:04:54.308 --> 00:04:56.978
Seriously. Hey, Woo Jae. What's up? Is something wrong?

00:04:58.518 --> 00:05:01.488
What? What do you mean Mom got hurt? Why?

00:05:04.048 --> 00:05:08.258
- She was hit by the director's mom? - What?

00:05:08.528 --> 00:05:09.528
Okay, I'm hanging up.

00:05:10.988 --> 00:05:12.198
What's going on?

00:05:13.198 --> 00:05:16.698
They found out everything. Looks like our parents had a fight.

00:05:17.928 --> 00:05:19.838
- Gosh, seriously. - No way...

00:05:25.578 --> 00:05:26.738
Yes, stepmom.

00:05:29.078 --> 00:05:32.548
What? Grandfather's in the ER? Why?

00:05:34.518 --> 00:05:37.518
Okay. I'll head home after work.

00:05:39.318 --> 00:05:40.788
What happened to your grandfather?

00:05:41.458 --> 00:05:43.628
It seems he witnessed the whole thing.

00:05:44.288 --> 00:05:46.458
He got emergency treatment and is on his way home now.

00:05:47.228 --> 00:05:48.228
This is unreal...

00:05:48.528 --> 00:05:51.738
How's your mother? Is she badly hurt?

00:05:51.838 --> 00:05:53.268
I'm not sure.

00:05:55.608 --> 00:05:57.168
Let's hurry home.

00:06:04.148 --> 00:06:05.978
I'm so sorry about this.

00:06:07.848 --> 00:06:11.458
Well, I don't think makeup can cover this...

00:06:13.288 --> 00:06:15.988
Of course. Yes, I'm all right.

00:06:16.728 --> 00:06:18.328
Okay. Again, I'm very sorry.

00:06:22.668 --> 00:06:26.298
Luckily, they had enough footage, so they told me to take the day off.

00:06:28.938 --> 00:06:29.938
Honey.

00:06:30.008 --> 00:06:32.978
Seriously, how could you hide this from me?

00:06:33.408 --> 00:06:35.908
It's about our family. Why didn't you tell me?

00:06:36.278 --> 00:06:37.378
Do you think I'm that...

00:06:37.708 --> 00:06:41.418
What, am I not part of this family? Why are you making me the bad guy?

00:06:41.748 --> 00:06:44.858
And you're supposed to be an expert on family matters.

00:06:44.918 --> 00:06:49.358
When a problem like this came up, your answer was to hide and lie?

00:06:54.898 --> 00:06:56.728
Gosh, I'm sorry. I am.

00:06:57.098 --> 00:06:59.938
It's just... I'm so furious, I feel like I'm going to burst.

00:07:01.438 --> 00:07:02.508
Let it all out.

00:07:03.208 --> 00:07:04.468
I'll listen to everything.

00:07:05.008 --> 00:07:06.338
I know how you feel...

00:07:07.108 --> 00:07:11.478
You feel hurt and betrayed. I understand.

00:07:11.778 --> 00:07:15.548
But for what it's worth, I was worried about both of you.

00:07:16.248 --> 00:07:17.918
I didn't want to see you and your brother get hurt.

00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:19.958
I know.

00:07:21.158 --> 00:07:25.628
I was trying to avoid bringing up the trauma from 30 years ago.

00:07:26.328 --> 00:07:31.068
Because the memory of that suffering is still so vivid.

00:07:31.598 --> 00:07:35.168
I was afraid that if rumors spread, we'd go through all that pain again.

00:07:36.138 --> 00:07:39.278
That's why I deliberately hid it from everyone.

00:07:40.208 --> 00:07:41.408
I'm sorry.

00:07:50.618 --> 00:07:52.718
I think I would've hidden it, too.

00:07:53.418 --> 00:07:55.158
How was she supposed to tell me?

00:07:57.058 --> 00:07:58.058
Mom.

00:07:58.528 --> 00:08:01.628
You know, back then... When Dad disappeared,

00:08:02.928 --> 00:08:05.238
I'd only ever thought about it from my perspective as a son.

00:08:05.998 --> 00:08:09.738
But now that I'm in your shoes, Mom...

00:08:11.008 --> 00:08:12.938
I realize how much harder it must have been for you...

00:08:14.038 --> 00:08:16.108
than we could ever have imagined.

00:08:16.508 --> 00:08:17.508
I'm sorry, Mom.

00:08:20.878 --> 00:08:23.418
Why did you have to learn what that feels like?

00:08:24.748 --> 00:08:27.958
You know, I've lived my life so I have nothing to be ashamed of.

00:08:28.658 --> 00:08:29.958
I had to live that way...

00:08:30.888 --> 00:08:33.698
so people wouldn't blame me for what happened.

00:08:34.698 --> 00:08:35.828
And I didn't want you boys...

00:08:36.968 --> 00:08:39.898
to hear people say, "No wonder your father ran off."

00:08:40.498 --> 00:08:42.408
So I always nagged you to live an upright life,

00:08:42.408 --> 00:08:43.968
even after you got older.

00:08:48.508 --> 00:08:50.878
But for this to happen to you...

00:08:52.518 --> 00:08:54.248
I just don't understand it.

00:08:56.588 --> 00:08:57.588
Mom.

00:08:58.758 --> 00:08:59.758
I'm okay.

00:09:12.798 --> 00:09:14.298
I'm truly sorry, Father.

00:09:14.938 --> 00:09:17.208
I made the whole thing up.

00:09:17.638 --> 00:09:19.738
You have every right to be furious with me.

00:09:25.218 --> 00:09:26.648
When did you find out?

00:09:27.578 --> 00:09:30.588
- Pardon? - Yong Gil and Dae Han's wife.

00:09:30.648 --> 00:09:32.918
When did you find out about their affair?

00:09:33.418 --> 00:09:35.788
Oh, that's...

00:09:36.188 --> 00:09:38.328
- I... - Father.

00:09:39.858 --> 00:09:40.898
What are you talking about?

00:09:41.628 --> 00:09:42.668
Honey.

00:09:43.828 --> 00:09:44.868
Yong Gil did what?

00:09:45.838 --> 00:09:47.268
Who did he have an affair with?

00:09:47.668 --> 00:09:48.968
Honey, it's just...

00:09:49.668 --> 00:09:50.738
Unbelievable.

00:09:51.638 --> 00:09:53.108
I'm going to kill them!

00:09:53.808 --> 00:09:55.908
You'd better stop him. Before he does something crazy.

00:09:57.508 --> 00:09:58.518
Honey.

00:10:03.848 --> 00:10:05.088
My husband?

00:10:06.188 --> 00:10:07.958
Of course, he has no idea.

00:10:09.558 --> 00:10:12.428
Okay, I get it. Then I'll see you tomorrow, darling.

00:10:12.698 --> 00:10:13.698
Bye!

00:10:16.668 --> 00:10:20.398
I had no idea her "darling" was my husband.

00:10:21.168 --> 00:10:22.168
Yang Dong Suk!

00:10:23.168 --> 00:10:24.268
What the heck is going on?

00:10:25.038 --> 00:10:27.808
Your husband cheated on you with Gong Dae Han's wife? For real?

00:10:28.848 --> 00:10:32.118
- Yes. - Wow! I'm seriously losing my mind.

00:10:32.678 --> 00:10:35.888
- What a complete disgrace! - Honey...

00:10:36.748 --> 00:10:38.688
What were you doing? How could you let him do it?

00:10:39.088 --> 00:10:42.228
What were you doing while that jerk was seeing her?

00:10:43.358 --> 00:10:45.598
- Is that my fault? - Then whose fault is it?

00:10:46.258 --> 00:10:49.528
Then I guess it was Dad's fault that our mom had an affair and left.

00:10:49.598 --> 00:10:51.428
Was it your fault you got divorced when your ex-wife...

00:10:51.428 --> 00:10:53.068
- cheated on you? - Hey!

00:10:53.068 --> 00:10:56.408
Honey, please stop. We can't fight among ourselves.

00:10:56.638 --> 00:10:59.038
Why did you bring trash like him into this family?

00:10:59.378 --> 00:11:03.208
- Why marry that jerk at all? - You told me to!

00:11:04.178 --> 00:11:07.248
You said you had to remarry, so you had to get your sister out.

00:11:07.248 --> 00:11:08.718
Just like you sent Hyun Bin to study abroad,

00:11:09.388 --> 00:11:11.758
you pushed me to get married and get out of the house!

00:11:12.118 --> 00:11:13.358
Dong Suk.

00:11:13.918 --> 00:11:16.388
It's not like I had great prospects, did I?

00:11:17.428 --> 00:11:20.058
Our mom ran off with the man who lived next door.

00:11:20.128 --> 00:11:22.968
So the guy I was dating dumped me, and I was turning into a spinster.

00:11:23.298 --> 00:11:24.828
And you have the nerve to say that?

00:11:25.238 --> 00:11:28.298
Hey! Don't you realize how critical this time is for me?

00:11:28.708 --> 00:11:31.338
And now, on top of everything, our families are tangled up again!

00:11:31.338 --> 00:11:32.638
Do I really have to hear this now?

00:11:32.708 --> 00:11:35.848
- Honey... - How is that my fault?

00:11:36.108 --> 00:11:38.978
How is any of that my fault?

00:11:40.118 --> 00:11:42.388
Right. It's not your fault, is it?

00:11:43.148 --> 00:11:44.348
How could this possibly be your fault?

00:11:46.258 --> 00:11:47.358
Honey.

00:12:00.668 --> 00:12:03.868
- Hey, watch it! You're annoying. - Sorry. My bad.

00:12:03.868 --> 00:12:05.378
Seriously...

00:12:14.978 --> 00:12:16.048
That jerk?

00:12:17.848 --> 00:12:18.988
So it was him.

00:12:31.198 --> 00:12:33.298
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:12:44.948 --> 00:12:45.948
Yes.

00:12:48.218 --> 00:12:49.288
Seong Mi.

00:12:50.048 --> 00:12:51.048
Are you feeling any better?

00:12:52.658 --> 00:12:54.558
I'll see how I feel tomorrow.

00:12:55.088 --> 00:12:58.658
You should've told me everything. Why did you go get hurt like this?

00:12:59.328 --> 00:13:01.228
I feel so terrible about this.

00:13:01.898 --> 00:13:04.568
Dae Han, I'm okay.

00:13:06.838 --> 00:13:08.468
Where did you find Hui Gyeong?

00:13:08.738 --> 00:13:10.538
And what are you going to do with that information?

00:13:11.308 --> 00:13:12.608
I just want to ask her a few things.

00:13:13.008 --> 00:13:15.408
Ask what? What is there left to ask?

00:13:15.778 --> 00:13:18.278
I'm just curious how she could do this to our family.

00:13:19.078 --> 00:13:20.078
And...

00:13:20.818 --> 00:13:23.318
I want to kill that jerk.

00:13:24.188 --> 00:13:25.218
Dae Han.

00:13:25.718 --> 00:13:27.118
I'll find her myself.

00:13:27.858 --> 00:13:30.988
Hey, Dae Han. Stop. Hey!

00:13:31.088 --> 00:13:32.958
Hey, let me go!

00:13:33.628 --> 00:13:35.198
- I'll handle this. - What?

00:13:35.198 --> 00:13:36.198
You stay out of it!

00:13:36.428 --> 00:13:38.898
- Why are they acting like this? - I said, let go of me!

00:13:39.038 --> 00:13:41.368
- Gong Dae Han, are you serious? - Let go!

00:13:41.368 --> 00:13:43.538
- Grandma, please rest. I'll check. - Where do you think you're going?

00:13:43.608 --> 00:13:46.508
Where else would she be? She's in Ganghwa! Right, Seong Mi?

00:13:46.578 --> 00:13:47.808
- Hey! - Please don't, Dae Han.

00:13:47.878 --> 00:13:49.708
- Let go of me! - What's wrong with everyone?

00:13:49.778 --> 00:13:52.178
Woo Jae. Right, you went there with her too, didn't you?

00:13:52.248 --> 00:13:54.848
- You know where they are, right? - Uncle.

00:13:54.918 --> 00:13:57.648
Woo Jae, please. You must tell me. I feel like I'm losing my mind.

00:13:57.718 --> 00:14:00.758
- Tell me! - Woo Jae, help me hold your uncle.

00:14:00.818 --> 00:14:03.128
- Let go! Don't touch me! Let go! - Uncle...

00:14:03.128 --> 00:14:04.188
- Uncle, please. - What's this?

00:14:04.258 --> 00:14:06.698
- Let go! - That jerk, Bucket, I swear...

00:14:06.758 --> 00:14:07.828
- Let go! - Don't answer it.

00:14:07.898 --> 00:14:09.628
- Hey, why not? - Don't answer it!

00:14:09.628 --> 00:14:10.868
Come on, why...

00:14:11.098 --> 00:14:14.338
- Darn it. Hey! - For the last time, let go of me!

00:14:19.908 --> 00:14:22.748
No answer? Are they ignoring my calls?

00:14:23.148 --> 00:14:26.378
Darn it. Hey, Gong Jeong Han! Gong Dae Han!

00:14:26.918 --> 00:14:28.018
Get out here, you two!

00:14:30.118 --> 00:14:31.848
- I think he's right outside. - Come out!

00:14:31.918 --> 00:14:32.988
That jerk, I swear.

00:14:33.058 --> 00:14:35.158
Stay here. I'll handle this. Just stay put.

00:14:35.218 --> 00:14:37.158
Where do you think you're going? You stay here. I'll go.

00:14:37.158 --> 00:14:40.058
- Just stay here. I said I'm going. - I'll handle this. Hey!

00:14:40.128 --> 00:14:41.798
- I told you to stop! - Don't you go out there!

00:14:44.368 --> 00:14:45.538
Hey, open this door!

00:14:46.168 --> 00:14:49.308
Hey, Gong Jeong Han! Gong Dae Han! Open the door!

00:14:54.938 --> 00:14:56.108
I said, open up!

00:14:56.778 --> 00:14:57.948
Dad!

00:14:58.208 --> 00:15:01.418
- Stop it! What are you doing? - What are you doing here?

00:15:02.148 --> 00:15:03.748
Hey, you. You're their daughter.

00:15:04.248 --> 00:15:08.158
- Can you open the door? Let me in. - And do what once you're inside?

00:15:08.218 --> 00:15:10.388
Listen, I have to talk to them.

00:15:10.388 --> 00:15:11.458
- Get out of my way! - No, wait...

00:15:11.488 --> 00:15:12.758
Hey, Gong Dae Han! Gong Jeong Han!

00:15:13.328 --> 00:15:14.898
- Get out here, you cowards! - This is insane.

00:15:15.328 --> 00:15:16.698
- Wait, Dad... - Get out here right now!

00:15:18.268 --> 00:15:20.138
- I'll let him in, Mom. - My goodness.

00:15:20.368 --> 00:15:22.668
- Okay. - Dad, what are you doing?

00:15:22.738 --> 00:15:23.738
I said, let go!

00:15:24.338 --> 00:15:25.638
Get out here, you cowards!

00:15:26.838 --> 00:15:28.138
He's coming in with Ju Ah.

00:15:28.238 --> 00:15:31.648
Coming in? Who said he could? The nerve of that man! Unbelievable!

00:15:31.748 --> 00:15:32.818
Gong Jeong Han! Gong Dae Han!

00:15:33.378 --> 00:15:34.578
You owe me an explanation.

00:15:35.078 --> 00:15:36.188
You jerk!

00:15:36.448 --> 00:15:38.958
How dare you barge into my house like you own the place?

00:15:39.488 --> 00:15:41.788
I'm so sorry. I tried to get him to leave, but...

00:15:42.028 --> 00:15:43.958
He's a director at my company. Dr. Yang's son.

00:15:44.058 --> 00:15:47.398
Oh, I'm Yang Hyun Bin. It's been a while.

00:15:47.998 --> 00:15:49.468
So what do you want?

00:15:49.898 --> 00:15:52.498
- Where did you hide your wife? - What did you just say?

00:15:52.568 --> 00:15:55.198
- Where did you hide your wife? - How am I supposed to know?

00:15:55.268 --> 00:15:56.408
Dad!

00:15:56.838 --> 00:15:57.838
Answer me, now!

00:15:58.338 --> 00:15:59.408
Then you tell me.

00:15:59.738 --> 00:16:00.808
You jerk.

00:16:00.878 --> 00:16:03.848
You barged in like this 30 years ago and harassed my mother,

00:16:04.008 --> 00:16:05.208
and now you're pulling the same stunt again?

00:16:05.278 --> 00:16:09.848
Right. So why does your family always start this nonsense?

00:16:10.418 --> 00:16:11.418
You jerk!

00:16:11.718 --> 00:16:14.418
You're the one who brought that woman into this neighborhood...

00:16:14.488 --> 00:16:15.628
and caused this whole mess!

00:16:15.688 --> 00:16:18.188
- This is all your fault! - How dare you talk to me like that!

00:16:18.258 --> 00:16:20.698
What? How is this my fault?

00:16:20.828 --> 00:16:22.728
Why do you always see us as the villains,

00:16:22.798 --> 00:16:25.128
and not as victims, just like you? Why can't you?

00:16:25.198 --> 00:16:27.538
Why do you always have to come here and act like a thug? Why?

00:16:27.598 --> 00:16:29.668
- What did you say, you punk? - Hey! Watch your mouth!

00:16:30.008 --> 00:16:32.978
Look what your wife did. I thought you came to apologize.

00:16:33.038 --> 00:16:36.048
- What? What did you say? - Mom.

00:16:36.778 --> 00:16:39.148
Hey, Seong Mi. Please, I'm begging you.

00:16:39.418 --> 00:16:41.978
Just tell me. Please? Where are they?

00:16:42.248 --> 00:16:44.548
- I'm begging you! Tell me! - Gosh, seriously...

00:16:44.618 --> 00:16:48.458
- Let's go, Dad, please. I'm sorry. - Hey, get off me!

00:16:48.518 --> 00:16:50.258
- Dad, come on! - Let go of me, you brat!

00:16:50.588 --> 00:16:54.898
- He's an animal. Unbelievable! - Hey!

00:16:55.258 --> 00:16:56.328
Good grief!

00:17:21.418 --> 00:17:22.428
Dad.

00:17:28.898 --> 00:17:30.068
Let's go inside.

00:17:31.028 --> 00:17:32.298
I need to blame someone.

00:17:32.598 --> 00:17:33.998
It's the only way I feel like I can survive.

00:17:35.168 --> 00:17:36.308
If it becomes my fault,

00:17:37.108 --> 00:17:38.508
I don't think I could bear it.

00:17:46.748 --> 00:17:48.518
Go inside and check on your grandfather and your aunt.

00:17:48.918 --> 00:17:51.388
Why? Are you going back to their house?

00:17:52.048 --> 00:17:53.058
No.

00:17:55.118 --> 00:17:57.088
It's just... I'm feeling a little suffocated.

00:17:58.188 --> 00:18:01.458
- I'll just sit here for a minute. - Wait. I'll stay with you.

00:18:02.428 --> 00:18:03.468
I want to be alone.

00:18:04.798 --> 00:18:06.738
I just need to catch my breath before I go inside.

00:18:09.938 --> 00:18:10.938
But...

00:18:17.878 --> 00:18:18.878
Auntie.

00:18:19.678 --> 00:18:22.748
Ji Hu's coming from the academy. Are you going to stay like this?

00:18:23.848 --> 00:18:24.948
Hello? Auntie.

00:18:34.828 --> 00:18:38.428
You were just going to leave me and run off like that, darling?

00:18:38.498 --> 00:18:41.538
Darling! Are you okay?

00:19:00.618 --> 00:19:03.928
Oh, boy. You'll ruin your pretty face.

00:19:05.128 --> 00:19:07.698
See? I told you to just wait patiently.

00:19:08.258 --> 00:19:12.438
I thought you were ditching me for Saudi Arabia.

00:19:12.498 --> 00:19:13.968
As if I'd ever do that.

00:19:14.338 --> 00:19:17.338
I was told not to call you around my kid, so I couldn't.

00:19:19.938 --> 00:19:20.938
Why?

00:19:28.948 --> 00:19:30.918
Hey. Does this look like Saudi Arabia?

00:19:30.988 --> 00:19:33.358
Dong Ik! Spare me, please!

00:19:33.418 --> 00:19:34.658
You jerk!

00:19:35.218 --> 00:19:36.428
You scumbag.

00:19:40.758 --> 00:19:41.898
You jerk!

00:19:42.228 --> 00:19:45.398
What did you promise my sister? You said you'd make Dong Suk happy.

00:19:45.468 --> 00:19:47.898
- Did you promise me or not? - I did.

00:19:48.038 --> 00:19:50.708
And what happened? You worked her to the bone...

00:19:50.768 --> 00:19:53.978
and made her nurse your sick mother until the day she died, didn't you?

00:19:54.038 --> 00:19:55.908
Then you blamed her for years...

00:19:56.008 --> 00:19:58.608
for not being able to conceive, until Ji Hu was born.

00:19:59.718 --> 00:20:02.318
You punk. You filthy jerk!

00:20:02.518 --> 00:20:06.018
And now, you abandon your family? How dare you?

00:20:06.688 --> 00:20:09.258
- Please, Dong Ik! Have mercy! - Get up!

00:20:10.588 --> 00:20:13.058
Are you even human? Are you?

00:20:13.358 --> 00:20:17.798
I still treated you like family! A good-for-nothing troublemaker...

00:20:17.868 --> 00:20:20.838
I gave you chance after chance! And yet,

00:20:20.898 --> 00:20:23.838
you dare pull a stunt like this? Hey!

00:20:24.808 --> 00:20:27.978
- Do you take our family for a joke? - No! I swear...

00:20:28.038 --> 00:20:30.108
If you didn't, then how could you do this?

00:20:31.808 --> 00:20:33.148
And with that woman, of all people?

00:20:34.078 --> 00:20:35.278
You jerk!

00:20:35.948 --> 00:20:37.048
Today...

00:20:37.888 --> 00:20:39.088
Only one of us is walking away from this!

00:20:39.988 --> 00:20:40.988
You!

00:20:41.658 --> 00:20:45.028
- Stop hitting him! - My family! Who do you take us for?

00:20:45.088 --> 00:20:46.658
- Darling! - It's time you suffered a little.

00:20:47.558 --> 00:20:50.698
You evil jerk. You worthless scumbag!

00:20:54.538 --> 00:20:57.068
Oh, man. I'm too ashamed to face my niece and nephew.

00:20:57.408 --> 00:20:59.338
It's okay, Uncle.

00:21:00.378 --> 00:21:02.348
He won't come back, will he?

00:21:02.508 --> 00:21:05.608
I dare him to. I'll tear him to shreds.

00:21:05.818 --> 00:21:06.818
He won't.

00:21:08.518 --> 00:21:10.518
I told him where they are.

00:21:19.128 --> 00:21:23.828
Hwangpo-ri 37-12, Ganghwa County. The hair salon on the first floor.

00:21:25.668 --> 00:21:26.668
Why did you do that?

00:21:27.468 --> 00:21:29.568
I have a bad feeling something's going to happen.

00:21:31.538 --> 00:21:33.008
I was going to talk to them first.

00:21:34.378 --> 00:21:36.278
And what good would that have done?

00:21:54.058 --> 00:21:55.158
Honey.

00:21:56.568 --> 00:21:59.038
You weren't answering your phone. Where have you...

00:22:01.438 --> 00:22:02.438
What?

00:22:03.908 --> 00:22:07.238
Where on earth have you been?

00:22:08.278 --> 00:22:09.378
Yong Gil.

00:22:10.278 --> 00:22:11.748
I had to go knock some sense into him.

00:22:16.188 --> 00:22:17.288
And?

00:22:18.188 --> 00:22:19.358
Feel better now?

00:22:21.658 --> 00:22:22.658
No.

00:22:41.908 --> 00:22:43.008
How's my father?

00:22:43.508 --> 00:22:45.818
Hyun Bin's with him, taking care of him.

00:22:48.118 --> 00:22:49.618
And how's Dong Suk doing?

00:22:50.088 --> 00:22:53.488
She's holed up in her room and won't eat anything.

00:22:54.418 --> 00:22:55.958
She won't even open the door.

00:23:32.798 --> 00:23:37.598
- What's everyone up to? - They're asleep. Why are you up?

00:23:39.838 --> 00:23:41.438
How could I possibly sleep?

00:23:42.768 --> 00:23:43.968
I know.

00:23:44.468 --> 00:23:47.178
Here, I brought some water in case you were thirsty.

00:23:47.738 --> 00:23:51.078
Thank you. I was just getting thirsty.

00:23:54.718 --> 00:23:57.148
Grandma. Are you okay?

00:23:59.558 --> 00:24:00.718
No.

00:24:01.588 --> 00:24:03.788
I know this is a lot to ask, but...

00:24:04.528 --> 00:24:06.328
we need you to hold it together.

00:24:08.898 --> 00:24:10.368
If you fall apart,

00:24:10.998 --> 00:24:12.738
we'll all fall apart, too.

00:24:16.038 --> 00:24:17.108
You're right.

00:24:19.008 --> 00:24:20.038
I should stay strong.

00:24:42.198 --> 00:24:44.298
(Director Yang Hyun Bin)

00:24:54.138 --> 00:24:56.908
The person you're trying to reach is unavailable. Please leave...

00:25:07.888 --> 00:25:10.888
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:25:12.728 --> 00:25:14.828
- Officer Jung. - Hello.

00:25:15.358 --> 00:25:16.828
Is the clinic open today?

00:25:16.968 --> 00:25:19.598
No. We were supposed to do medical volunteering today,

00:25:19.668 --> 00:25:20.668
but we decided to take the day off.

00:25:21.598 --> 00:25:23.768
Then what brings you in, Nurse Oh?

00:25:24.538 --> 00:25:27.078
I came in to finish the cleaning I couldn't get to yesterday.

00:25:29.108 --> 00:25:31.678
- I'll let you get to it. - Okay, have a good day!

00:25:38.818 --> 00:25:42.158
Give me that. Larceny is a violation of Criminal Code Article 329.

00:25:42.218 --> 00:25:45.228
"A clash between the families erupts after the affair is exposed."

00:25:47.898 --> 00:25:50.568
So you knew all along.

00:25:50.728 --> 00:25:53.438
This horrible tragedy that's struck these rival families again.

00:25:54.898 --> 00:25:57.138
It's not like I wanted to know.

00:25:57.938 --> 00:26:00.978
Does anyone else know about this?

00:26:01.478 --> 00:26:03.848
No. Just the chief and me.

00:26:04.248 --> 00:26:08.248
- What a relief. This can't get out. - Understood.

00:26:08.478 --> 00:26:09.618
Wait, but...

00:26:10.988 --> 00:26:13.518
We should be fine, as long as you can keep it quiet.

00:26:15.618 --> 00:26:17.758
- Really? - Yes.

00:26:17.828 --> 00:26:19.828
Anyway, it's a secret.

00:26:20.458 --> 00:26:21.498
It is a secret.

00:26:27.098 --> 00:26:29.338
Do you think the doctor's eye will be okay?

00:26:30.438 --> 00:26:31.438
Yes, I wonder.

00:26:34.408 --> 00:26:35.408
Hey.

00:26:35.778 --> 00:26:38.208
They'll hate us even more, right? More than they already did.

00:26:39.048 --> 00:26:42.748
I'll be honest. Who could ever like our grandfather and our dad?

00:26:42.848 --> 00:26:45.218
Even their wives couldn't stand them and ran off.

00:26:45.718 --> 00:26:48.718
It's hopeless for us. We're doomed. Totally doomed.

00:26:49.828 --> 00:26:51.058
I'm off.

00:26:51.228 --> 00:26:54.258
What? Going to class? Hey, eat some breakfast first.

00:26:54.798 --> 00:26:56.768
It's okay. I'm not hungry.

00:26:57.428 --> 00:26:59.838
Come eat even if you don't feel like it.

00:27:02.908 --> 00:27:03.908
Here.

00:27:04.938 --> 00:27:05.938
How's your mom?

00:27:06.338 --> 00:27:07.838
She's just staying in bed.

00:27:08.208 --> 00:27:12.408
Well, her husband suddenly left for Saudi Arabia,

00:27:12.478 --> 00:27:16.548
- so that would be hard on anyone. - Hey, I know everything.

00:27:16.818 --> 00:27:18.518
That Dad had an affair and left home.

00:27:19.018 --> 00:27:22.188
And you're this calm about it? Wow, you're something else.

00:27:22.258 --> 00:27:27.098
- My brother cried every day. - Yes, a tough kid. A real man.

00:27:27.228 --> 00:27:30.298
Hyun Bin. You won't take over the clinic, will you?

00:27:30.398 --> 00:27:33.138
No. Please, I'm begging you to take it.

00:27:34.338 --> 00:27:37.608
Look at this ambitious man. Go for it.

00:27:38.538 --> 00:27:41.078
Hey, where's our stepmom?

00:27:41.538 --> 00:27:42.878
She left early.

00:27:43.248 --> 00:27:44.708
This early? Where did she go?

00:27:57.358 --> 00:28:00.458
A new person may enter, but they will not be able to settle.

00:28:01.428 --> 00:28:04.098
Anything you try to hold onto will slip away.

00:28:04.798 --> 00:28:08.198
The energy of a fiery misfortune is deeply entangled with you!

00:28:09.608 --> 00:28:10.708
Shaman,

00:28:11.238 --> 00:28:16.078
then what can I do to prevent this misfortune?

00:28:17.048 --> 00:28:20.818
Hold on. Let me ask the spirits.

00:28:33.458 --> 00:28:35.458
I see something round.

00:28:36.398 --> 00:28:37.568
Something round?

00:28:42.298 --> 00:28:43.568
Round...

00:28:45.438 --> 00:28:47.778
It looks like a ball.

00:28:47.778 --> 00:28:49.708
A ball?

00:28:50.208 --> 00:28:51.278
A ball?

00:28:51.878 --> 00:28:54.248
Yes. Stay away from balls.

00:28:57.848 --> 00:28:58.848
Oh, my.

00:29:00.388 --> 00:29:01.388
The Gongs?

00:29:01.458 --> 00:29:05.728
Yes, Father. I didn't say a word about that family,

00:29:05.758 --> 00:29:08.828
but she pointedly told me to stay away from "balls."

00:29:08.898 --> 00:29:12.268
Balls? What else could it mean but the Gongs?

00:29:12.868 --> 00:29:15.298
Stepmom, that sounds like a bit of a stretch.

00:29:15.368 --> 00:29:18.838
No, what happened 30 years ago is repeating itself.

00:29:19.068 --> 00:29:21.978
This is no mere coincidence. This is clearly...

00:29:22.808 --> 00:29:24.248
a warning from the heavens.

00:29:52.008 --> 00:29:55.608
Gosh, this is going to scar. Seriously, what is this?

00:29:56.248 --> 00:29:57.478
You sound just like a doctor.

00:29:58.148 --> 00:29:59.378
How can you be joking right now?

00:30:00.518 --> 00:30:01.518
That's my point.

00:30:03.018 --> 00:30:05.818
No one does this without a grudge, right?

00:30:06.018 --> 00:30:08.688
I could feel the pure malice in her touch.

00:30:09.258 --> 00:30:11.188
No, come on.

00:30:11.888 --> 00:30:15.158
She's not that bad of a person, is she?

00:30:15.298 --> 00:30:19.428
Did you forget I was almost branded a homewrecker because of her?

00:30:25.168 --> 00:30:27.878
Don't you think you should apologize to Dr. Han Seong Mi?

00:30:28.138 --> 00:30:31.848
It looks like she was badly hurt. I know it was an accident, but...

00:30:34.718 --> 00:30:35.748
Maybe...

00:30:37.118 --> 00:30:39.218
I might have done it on purpose.

00:30:43.088 --> 00:30:44.428
Sorry to disappoint you.

00:30:46.328 --> 00:30:48.358
Why? Why would you do that?

00:30:50.468 --> 00:30:51.468
It's because...

00:30:52.698 --> 00:30:54.138
I really can't stand that woman.

00:30:56.338 --> 00:30:58.368
Your father is my entire world.

00:30:59.108 --> 00:31:00.978
But the man who means the world to me...

00:31:02.278 --> 00:31:04.248
gets completely flustered whenever he's around her.

00:31:05.208 --> 00:31:06.618
And you know, that just...

00:31:07.248 --> 00:31:09.118
makes me so angry and jealous.

00:31:11.748 --> 00:31:12.748
And so...

00:31:13.388 --> 00:31:16.018
I hate that woman even more than your birth mother,

00:31:17.788 --> 00:31:19.058
who gave you and Eun Bin life.

00:31:32.638 --> 00:31:33.878
About what my stepmother did...

00:31:34.438 --> 00:31:35.938
I'd like to apologize on her behalf.

00:31:37.348 --> 00:31:38.348
Okay.

00:31:38.908 --> 00:31:40.518
I'll pass that along to my mom.

00:31:45.748 --> 00:31:47.218
This is all so difficult.

00:31:49.928 --> 00:31:53.498
What happened to all that confidence about "rebranding" your family?

00:31:55.498 --> 00:31:57.798
I guess I was just being overconfident.

00:31:58.928 --> 00:32:01.338
This is why I gave up and went to study abroad back then.

00:32:01.698 --> 00:32:03.108
It just brought all those memories back.

00:32:06.738 --> 00:32:07.738
Hyun Bin.

00:32:14.778 --> 00:32:15.778
Yes?

00:32:17.588 --> 00:32:18.588
You know...

00:32:20.418 --> 00:32:25.128
My grandma, my dad, and my mom. My uncle and my little brother.

00:32:25.828 --> 00:32:26.958
All of my family.

00:32:27.858 --> 00:32:30.068
I think I love them...

00:32:30.898 --> 00:32:32.368
more than I ever realized.

00:32:37.568 --> 00:32:38.568
I know.

00:32:39.638 --> 00:32:40.638
And...

00:32:42.008 --> 00:32:43.078
I...

00:32:43.678 --> 00:32:47.518
I don't think my feelings for you...

00:32:50.448 --> 00:32:51.448
are stronger...

00:32:52.048 --> 00:32:53.918
than my love for my family.

00:33:01.128 --> 00:33:02.228
Right now,

00:33:03.468 --> 00:33:05.428
my family is already hurting so much.

00:33:06.128 --> 00:33:09.668
I can't bring myself...

00:33:10.968 --> 00:33:11.968
to hurt them even more.

00:33:14.838 --> 00:33:15.838
Okay.

00:33:24.888 --> 00:33:26.388
I appreciate your feelings,

00:33:27.858 --> 00:33:29.018
and I'm sorry...

00:33:30.028 --> 00:33:31.028
for turning you down.

00:33:41.838 --> 00:33:43.438
No, I'm sorry for confessing...

00:33:46.138 --> 00:33:47.478
and making things so hard on you.

00:34:02.958 --> 00:34:05.128
(Ms. Na Seon Hae)

00:34:10.828 --> 00:34:11.828
(Ms. Na Seon Hae)

00:34:19.708 --> 00:34:20.978
Yes, Ms. Na.

00:34:27.218 --> 00:34:28.818
It's been such a long time...

00:34:29.478 --> 00:34:31.118
since we've sat face-to-face.

00:34:32.118 --> 00:34:33.118
It really has.

00:34:35.918 --> 00:34:38.428
How did it come to this?

00:34:39.828 --> 00:34:40.998
And to think, you were the one...

00:34:42.058 --> 00:34:43.728
who named my children.

00:34:45.298 --> 00:34:46.298
I did.

00:34:48.098 --> 00:34:50.508
And your husband named Dong Ik.

00:34:53.278 --> 00:34:56.108
We used to make kimchi together every winter,

00:34:56.848 --> 00:34:59.108
share meals of steamed pork and oysters,

00:34:59.818 --> 00:35:04.048
and take trips to the creek every summer.

00:35:05.488 --> 00:35:07.718
We all piled into a rented van...

00:35:08.518 --> 00:35:11.428
to see the opening ceremony of the 1988 Summer Sporting Event.

00:35:12.558 --> 00:35:13.598
That's right.

00:35:14.258 --> 00:35:16.498
We all wore matching Hodori the Tiger shirts.

00:35:26.008 --> 00:35:27.408
I never dreamed...

00:35:28.338 --> 00:35:31.148
the same thing would happen to our kids.

00:35:32.378 --> 00:35:33.478
For everyone's sake,

00:35:35.418 --> 00:35:36.788
I suppose it's best...

00:35:38.048 --> 00:35:39.448
if our families go their separate ways.

00:35:41.818 --> 00:35:42.818
Yes.

00:35:44.188 --> 00:35:47.398
This long bond between us... No, this twisted fate.

00:35:48.758 --> 00:35:50.468
It's time we cut ties for good.

00:36:01.008 --> 00:36:02.378
Mom, you want us to move?

00:36:02.638 --> 00:36:05.248
What? Why should we? What did we do wrong?

00:36:06.408 --> 00:36:09.548
If we had moved away sooner, this never would have happened.

00:36:09.818 --> 00:36:12.348
No, Mom, that's not it. It was just a coincidence.

00:36:12.588 --> 00:36:16.288
And there's no guarantee we won't get tangled up with them again.

00:36:17.188 --> 00:36:20.728
Seriously? How could that happen? Unbelievable.

00:36:20.798 --> 00:36:24.228
But we don't have anywhere to go right now.

00:36:25.028 --> 00:36:26.898
I'll figure something out.

00:36:27.568 --> 00:36:31.268
- I'll chip in. I can get a loan. - Now, hold on.

00:36:31.508 --> 00:36:35.408
We haven't decided that we're moving.

00:36:35.908 --> 00:36:38.548
They said they'd think about it, too.

00:36:38.778 --> 00:36:42.318
Gosh, there's no way that jerk is moving.

00:36:43.078 --> 00:36:44.248
Darn it.

00:36:45.948 --> 00:36:47.118
I'm absolutely not moving.

00:36:48.118 --> 00:36:49.818
You don't want to move either, do you, Dad?

00:36:50.688 --> 00:36:51.758
The whole thing blew over quietly.

00:36:52.358 --> 00:36:53.458
No one in town is talking about it.

00:36:54.728 --> 00:36:55.828
But still,

00:36:56.868 --> 00:37:00.368
I don't think I can work seeing that family every single day.

00:37:00.798 --> 00:37:03.968
Then, couldn't you just find a new job?

00:37:05.068 --> 00:37:08.978
Fine, do whatever you want. What say do I have in this?

00:37:09.978 --> 00:37:11.948
I don't want to move or switch schools either.

00:37:12.408 --> 00:37:14.878
Right. No one in town knows, so don't worry.

00:37:15.748 --> 00:37:17.118
Everyone thinks your dad just went to Saudi Arabia.

00:37:18.318 --> 00:37:22.158
Father, I completely agree that our families should separate, but...

00:37:22.388 --> 00:37:25.688
I don't think us being the ones to leave Onjeong is the right move.

00:37:26.188 --> 00:37:28.358
What about all the money we spent renovating the clinic?

00:37:28.758 --> 00:37:32.368
Besides, Father, you know how hard he's been working lately.

00:37:32.868 --> 00:37:35.398
He's just now winning over the people at the market.

00:37:35.398 --> 00:37:37.208
We can't give up now.

00:37:38.508 --> 00:37:41.308
It's not that we've decided to move.

00:37:43.208 --> 00:37:45.208
We've simply agreed that both sides will think it over.

00:37:56.788 --> 00:37:58.628
Did you talk to my dad about moving?

00:37:59.258 --> 00:38:02.698
Yes, I suggested that we should make the Gong family move.

00:38:03.058 --> 00:38:06.068
I'm going to make sure the Gongs leave Onjeong this time.

00:38:06.738 --> 00:38:07.738
Yes, we should.

00:38:08.738 --> 00:38:09.738
And when that happens,

00:38:10.138 --> 00:38:12.868
you'll become the President of the Merchants' Association.

00:38:13.638 --> 00:38:15.378
- You think so? - Of course.

00:38:15.378 --> 00:38:18.078
Nothing's a safer bet than getting rid of the competition.

00:38:19.308 --> 00:38:22.618
Honey, let's turn this crisis into an opportunity.

00:38:24.618 --> 00:38:27.918
But I doubt Jeong Han's family will move.

00:38:28.558 --> 00:38:30.258
We'll have to make them move, one way or another.

00:38:30.888 --> 00:38:31.988
Leave it to me, honey.

00:38:42.068 --> 00:38:43.068
Well...

00:38:43.668 --> 00:38:46.308
This is a gift certificate for a spa.

00:38:46.838 --> 00:38:48.378
If you get a treatment there,

00:38:48.478 --> 00:38:51.908
it should help that bruise of yours fade faster.

00:38:52.378 --> 00:38:56.348
- You hit me on purpose, didn't you? - Oh, my goodness! Of course not!

00:38:56.718 --> 00:38:58.418
Really, you've got it all wrong.

00:39:00.018 --> 00:39:03.358
I also included more than enough to cover any medical fees.

00:39:04.258 --> 00:39:05.258
That won't be necessary.

00:39:05.758 --> 00:39:09.828
I just put some ointment on it. The bruise will fade soon enough.

00:39:10.428 --> 00:39:14.538
Please, I insist, Doctor. It's a small token of my apology.

00:39:17.608 --> 00:39:18.908
I'll accept the gesture.

00:39:19.968 --> 00:39:23.448
- Is that everything? - Wait. Actually...

00:39:24.008 --> 00:39:26.918
I went to see a really gifted psychic.

00:39:27.378 --> 00:39:30.488
She said that our two families are like oil and water.

00:39:30.848 --> 00:39:32.488
You needed a psychic to tell you that?

00:39:33.588 --> 00:39:34.858
To be honest,

00:39:35.488 --> 00:39:37.588
I think it's for the best if your family moves.

00:39:38.188 --> 00:39:41.598
Doctor, your clinic is in Seoul, and your daughter works in Seoul.

00:39:41.998 --> 00:39:43.698
Also, wouldn't it be better...

00:39:43.698 --> 00:39:46.198
for Dr. Gong to practice in Seoul as well?

00:39:46.898 --> 00:39:49.898
The elders will decide, so let's just wait.

00:39:50.238 --> 00:39:53.638
Doctor, please try to convince Dr. Gong.

00:39:53.938 --> 00:39:58.308
We can't change the past, but shouldn't we prevent things?

00:39:59.278 --> 00:40:02.548
I'm worried that if this continues, our kids will get tangled up in it.

00:40:02.748 --> 00:40:06.088
- I'm just so worried. - That kind of thing...

00:40:07.058 --> 00:40:08.988
will never happen.

00:40:11.628 --> 00:40:15.258
I certainly hope not. I'm desperately hoping you're right.

00:40:21.098 --> 00:40:24.738
(Taehan Group)

00:40:43.388 --> 00:40:46.158
(Fantom)

00:40:55.468 --> 00:40:56.498
I was wondering...

00:40:57.238 --> 00:41:00.208
Have you heard any talk at home about moving?

00:41:02.138 --> 00:41:06.048
I'm sorry, but let's not discuss personal matters at the office.

00:41:10.848 --> 00:41:11.848
Right, Director.

00:41:23.528 --> 00:41:24.528
Director.

00:41:31.908 --> 00:41:33.068
Oh, Director.

00:41:37.408 --> 00:41:38.508
Hello.

00:41:41.278 --> 00:41:42.878
What's with him? Why isn't he joining us?

00:41:43.988 --> 00:41:45.348
He was acting like that this morning, too.

00:41:46.748 --> 00:41:47.758
Did you two have a fight?

00:41:48.618 --> 00:41:49.618
Just eat.

00:41:57.898 --> 00:41:59.128
As you may have heard,

00:41:59.468 --> 00:42:03.668
we're considering Dr. Han Seong Mi to be the face of FG next season.

00:42:04.368 --> 00:42:05.838
Before we make a formal offer,

00:42:06.108 --> 00:42:07.878
I wanted to hear what our designers think.

00:42:09.408 --> 00:42:10.708
Dr. Han Seong Mi?

00:42:12.448 --> 00:42:16.418
But she doesn't have any modeling or brand sponsorship experience.

00:42:18.118 --> 00:42:19.348
What are your thoughts, Mr. Park?

00:42:19.718 --> 00:42:22.218
I'm a huge fan of hers.

00:42:22.918 --> 00:42:26.588
I think she'd be a great fit for the mood of our next collection.

00:42:26.758 --> 00:42:29.828
Exactly. Uniqueness gives a premium image,

00:42:29.828 --> 00:42:31.528
so I think she's a great choice.

00:42:33.668 --> 00:42:36.038
But why have you two been so quiet this whole time?

00:42:37.238 --> 00:42:38.268
Did you two get in a fight?

00:42:43.408 --> 00:42:46.918
Vice President, I apologize for bringing this up at work.

00:42:47.678 --> 00:42:49.518
We tried our best to make things work,

00:42:49.918 --> 00:42:51.188
but it just didn't pan out.

00:42:51.948 --> 00:42:55.418
What? Why? What happened? Tell me. Come on.

00:42:55.518 --> 00:42:57.888
We've decided to keep things strictly professional from now on,

00:42:58.758 --> 00:43:00.958
so please treat us as such. We would appreciate it.

00:43:01.598 --> 00:43:05.198
(Taehan Group)

00:43:09.298 --> 00:43:13.708
You don't think the Director's mom hit your mom on purpose, do you?

00:43:13.938 --> 00:43:15.338
When two people hate each other,

00:43:15.608 --> 00:43:17.748
the truth doesn't really matter.

00:43:19.978 --> 00:43:23.148
Man, this is going to make it tough for her to be our model.

00:43:23.688 --> 00:43:26.788
She has to work with the Director, not just you, you know.

00:43:27.418 --> 00:43:28.688
Right.

00:43:31.028 --> 00:43:33.458
You look really upset, Ju Ah.

00:43:33.858 --> 00:43:38.498
Gosh. Maybe it was better when I pretended not to know.

00:43:40.168 --> 00:43:41.168
Hey,

00:43:41.538 --> 00:43:43.568
this might sound a bit insensitive, but can I ask something?

00:43:43.708 --> 00:43:44.708
Sure, go ahead.

00:43:45.208 --> 00:43:46.768
So, which family is moving?

00:43:47.238 --> 00:43:48.578
Wouldn't it be better if your family moved?

00:43:48.978 --> 00:43:51.878
Your mom's clinic is around here, so it'd be great if you moved here.

00:43:52.978 --> 00:43:56.448
If it were that simple, we would've moved already.

00:43:57.718 --> 00:43:59.018
Oh, boy.

00:44:08.228 --> 00:44:09.228
So, what do you think?

00:44:10.058 --> 00:44:14.068
- Where did you get it done? - I got a haircut. Is it okay?

00:44:14.138 --> 00:44:15.538
You have to tell me where that salon is.

00:44:15.598 --> 00:44:18.438
Wow, your joints have gotten so much more flexible.

00:44:18.668 --> 00:44:20.038
I see that. And no fluid buildup, either.

00:44:20.438 --> 00:44:21.808
And you're in less pain, right?

00:44:21.908 --> 00:44:25.308
Of course. I've been sleeping so well lately,

00:44:25.508 --> 00:44:26.548
and I feel alive again.

00:44:27.748 --> 00:44:31.448
Weren't you moving to the country? When is that?

00:44:31.518 --> 00:44:36.218
- What? I've already moved. - Oh, really? Go to a closer clinic.

00:44:36.288 --> 00:44:37.728
Why come all the way out here?

00:44:38.028 --> 00:44:39.028
Honestly.

00:44:39.358 --> 00:44:42.398
There are no clinics out there. This is the closest one.

00:44:43.428 --> 00:44:45.928
Oh, right.

00:44:46.598 --> 00:44:48.238
Yes, there aren't any others, are there?

00:44:49.098 --> 00:44:50.368
Oh, goodness.

00:44:54.608 --> 00:44:55.838
- Bye. - Get home safely.

00:44:56.108 --> 00:44:58.148
- Okay, see you again. - Yes, of course.

00:44:58.208 --> 00:44:59.208
Take care.

00:44:59.808 --> 00:45:02.018
- Doctor. - Yes? What is it?

00:45:03.478 --> 00:45:06.988
The patients know our 40th anniversary is coming up,

00:45:06.988 --> 00:45:08.258
and they're planning a party.

00:45:08.758 --> 00:45:11.758
- A party? - I couldn't help but overhear.

00:45:12.128 --> 00:45:13.458
You know, like a surprise party?

00:45:14.028 --> 00:45:15.158
I think they're planning one.

00:45:25.568 --> 00:45:29.338
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:45:33.178 --> 00:45:34.178
Hey.

00:45:35.018 --> 00:45:37.318
Don't insist on us moving just for my sake.

00:45:39.118 --> 00:45:43.188
But are you really okay, having to face them every day?

00:45:44.558 --> 00:45:46.088
I'll get used to it, I guess.

00:45:47.058 --> 00:45:49.858
Then, how about you just transfer to a different clinic?

00:45:50.298 --> 00:45:53.168
- Honestly, many clinics want you. - Oh, come on.

00:45:53.628 --> 00:45:56.238
If I wanted to leave, I would've left a long time ago.

00:45:57.768 --> 00:46:00.878
I'm not a doctor, but I want to carry on the family legacy...

00:46:00.938 --> 00:46:03.308
and keep this clinic going just as much as you do.

00:46:03.308 --> 00:46:04.508
So let's not do anything rash.

00:46:05.478 --> 00:46:07.348
Besides, we can't afford to move anyway,

00:46:08.118 --> 00:46:09.578
and it would just be hard on your wife.

00:46:10.748 --> 00:46:11.888
You know what I mean, right?

00:46:14.288 --> 00:46:18.688
I don't know anymore. Man, I don't know what to do.

00:46:27.568 --> 00:46:31.068
Wow, how do you manage to look so dapper in everything?

00:46:31.138 --> 00:46:35.078
- You look so handsome. - Gosh, but I'm getting nervous.

00:46:35.638 --> 00:46:36.908
I think I need something to calm my nerves.

00:46:36.978 --> 00:46:39.508
Honey, no matter what happens, don't get worked up.

00:46:39.678 --> 00:46:42.718
And for the photos, make sure you're right in the center, okay?

00:46:42.778 --> 00:46:45.588
This interview is basically your portfolio.

00:46:45.818 --> 00:46:49.458
Don't worry. I've learned the practice questions.

00:46:50.158 --> 00:46:54.498
Emphasize the Night Market Project and the self-service complaint desk.

00:46:55.198 --> 00:46:56.198
Okay.

00:46:57.698 --> 00:46:59.798
- Looking good. - You think so?

00:47:01.638 --> 00:47:04.908
Let's get you a new outfit. You're always wearing dark colors.

00:47:05.568 --> 00:47:08.778
When you're this handsome, no one cares about your clothes.

00:47:09.908 --> 00:47:11.548
Did you prepare for the interview?

00:47:12.108 --> 00:47:15.878
What's there to prepare? It's only real if I speak my mind.

00:47:16.418 --> 00:47:19.948
Only amateurs need to practice. Right? Fools like Bucket.

00:47:21.318 --> 00:47:24.828
I've always dreamed of serving the Merchants' Association.

00:47:25.088 --> 00:47:26.458
The permanent market...

00:47:26.788 --> 00:47:30.728
Man, look at that outfit. Are you off to a cabaret?

00:47:30.798 --> 00:47:32.898
Hey, who even says "cabaret" anymore?

00:47:32.998 --> 00:47:35.798
And what about you? Are you headed to a funeral?

00:47:36.068 --> 00:47:40.108
Gosh, you look so drab. Go make real money in Seoul already.

00:47:40.238 --> 00:47:44.278
You're one to talk. Stop putting on airs in this town.

00:47:44.548 --> 00:47:48.718
- You should move. - Not a chance. You move.

00:47:48.778 --> 00:47:53.018
On second thought, it suits you. You could tour cabarets nationwide.

00:47:53.088 --> 00:47:55.218
Are you on a blind date? At least make an effort.

00:47:55.288 --> 00:47:57.088
Some people succeed for a reason, buddy.

00:47:57.218 --> 00:47:59.258
- Oh, hello. - Hello.

00:47:59.328 --> 00:48:00.358
- Hello. - Hello.

00:48:00.358 --> 00:48:02.258
I'm Yang Dong Ik. I hold a key position at the association.

00:48:02.328 --> 00:48:04.898
- Hello. - I'm Gong Jeong Han,

00:48:04.898 --> 00:48:06.898
the President of the Onjeong Market Merchants' Association.

00:48:06.928 --> 00:48:08.998
- Nice to meet you. - Likewise.

00:48:10.168 --> 00:48:12.738
- Shall we begin the interview? - Yes.

00:48:14.138 --> 00:48:18.748
You're new as president, Dr. Gong, but you're handling complaints...

00:48:18.808 --> 00:48:21.548
and cleaning up the market. I hear you've had amazing results.

00:48:22.618 --> 00:48:26.748
I wouldn't call them results. It's just my duty to the market.

00:48:26.888 --> 00:48:30.158
He just gives the orders. I'm the one who does the legwork.

00:48:30.958 --> 00:48:31.988
Is that so?

00:48:32.628 --> 00:48:34.658
And I hear you're also preparing the Night Market Project?

00:48:34.728 --> 00:48:35.898
Yes, the Night Market...

00:48:35.958 --> 00:48:40.028
That's my campaign promise. I'm leading the project.

00:48:40.798 --> 00:48:44.438
My, you two seem to be perfectly in sync.

00:48:44.508 --> 00:48:47.738
I wouldn't call it "perfectly in sync."

00:48:48.338 --> 00:48:50.408
He's very lacking and inexperienced,

00:48:50.478 --> 00:48:53.648
but I'm leading the way and teaching him as we go.

00:48:54.448 --> 00:48:58.618
Dr. Gong is just so naive and inflexible.

00:48:58.888 --> 00:49:01.458
So I'm the one who provides the reality check.

00:49:01.588 --> 00:49:04.988
Dr. Yang focuses only on tangible results,

00:49:05.158 --> 00:49:09.498
so I'm the one who helps merchants and keeps the market grounded.

00:49:10.228 --> 00:49:12.728
You two really are a dream team, aren't you?

00:49:13.328 --> 00:49:15.838
I heard you two have been friends since childhood.

00:49:15.898 --> 00:49:18.938
- No, we're not friends. - No, just classmates.

00:49:19.238 --> 00:49:20.838
Strictly classmates.

00:49:20.908 --> 00:49:23.908
From elementary school to college. So, yes, classmates.

00:49:25.648 --> 00:49:29.618
- That's quite a special connection. - I guess you could say that.

00:49:29.778 --> 00:49:32.618
Back in school, I was always the class president,

00:49:32.918 --> 00:49:37.728
and he was always my vice president. Yes, that's right.

00:49:38.388 --> 00:49:40.388
Hey, I was class president too, you know.

00:49:40.658 --> 00:49:42.898
Hey, let's be real. I let you win back then.

00:49:43.658 --> 00:49:44.928
Let me win? As if.

00:49:45.198 --> 00:49:48.398
Hey, since we were kids, no matter what game we played,

00:49:48.468 --> 00:49:49.898
I always beat you.

00:49:51.108 --> 00:49:52.908
He's completely rewriting history.

00:49:53.408 --> 00:49:55.938
- I always won. - Unbelievable.

00:49:56.008 --> 00:49:58.408
You two certainly share a lot of memories.

00:49:58.478 --> 00:50:00.848
I'm sure you have even more interesting stories.

00:50:00.918 --> 00:50:02.578
We do.

00:50:03.018 --> 00:50:05.948
Ma'am, do you happen to know his nickname?

00:50:08.818 --> 00:50:11.388
Hey, don't. Don't you dare.

00:50:12.288 --> 00:50:14.458
The Man in the Red Underwear.

00:50:15.328 --> 00:50:16.328
I'm sorry?

00:50:17.568 --> 00:50:18.628
Have you lost your mind?

00:50:19.128 --> 00:50:21.468
He has a tendency to make things up. Please don't print that.

00:50:22.368 --> 00:50:26.838
He once climbed the wall at Seodong Girls' High for a crush.

00:50:27.008 --> 00:50:28.538
Hey, shut it.

00:50:28.608 --> 00:50:33.148
But his pants ripped wide open, revealing his bright red undies.

00:50:33.208 --> 00:50:35.678
Hey! They were red long johns!

00:50:35.748 --> 00:50:37.348
I'm telling you, they weren't undies! Seriously.

00:50:38.418 --> 00:50:40.188
That's even funnier. Same difference.

00:50:40.618 --> 00:50:41.918
This is great.

00:50:42.718 --> 00:50:46.888
You think that's funny? How about I tell one about our VP?

00:50:47.028 --> 00:50:49.328
What story? There's nothing to tell. I wouldn't do that if I were you.

00:50:49.558 --> 00:50:53.268
Well, our VP has a rather weak stomach.

00:50:53.328 --> 00:50:55.068
- To this day, when he's out, - Hey. Will you shut your mouth?

00:50:55.138 --> 00:50:56.698
- he can't go number two. - Stop it.

00:50:57.038 --> 00:51:00.208
- Seriously... - On a class trip, he held it in...

00:51:00.268 --> 00:51:01.278
- and let it go in his pants. - Hey!

00:51:01.338 --> 00:51:03.308
He just pooped right in his pants.

00:51:04.548 --> 00:51:08.048
Hey! You promised you'd take that to the grave.

00:51:08.118 --> 00:51:09.978
Well, consider this your funeral.

00:51:11.348 --> 00:51:14.088
No, back when I was a kid, I just misjudged a fart...

00:51:14.288 --> 00:51:15.318
He can't tell a fart from...

00:51:21.528 --> 00:51:24.798
Where did he go? Why isn't he here? We're going to be late at this rate.

00:51:26.228 --> 00:51:27.638
My goodness.

00:51:32.408 --> 00:51:35.208
Hi, Mr. Yang. Where are you? We have the buyers meeting today.

00:51:35.538 --> 00:51:38.878
I'm on my way to the meeting. Make sure you're not late.

00:51:40.348 --> 00:51:41.878
Yes, Mr. Yang. I understand.

00:51:43.548 --> 00:51:45.988
What the... He could've warned me. Seriously.

00:51:47.148 --> 00:51:49.618
Then again, it's not like he's my chauffeur.

00:51:50.758 --> 00:51:54.398
What were you thinking, Ju Ah? I'm going to be late.

00:51:54.998 --> 00:51:56.058
I've got to hurry.

00:52:07.678 --> 00:52:09.238
Were you not aware of the meeting time?

00:52:09.578 --> 00:52:12.908
I was, I'm so sorry. I thought we were going together.

00:52:14.878 --> 00:52:16.378
I had other meetings outside the office.

00:52:16.818 --> 00:52:18.818
I wasn't aware I had to report my every move to you.

00:52:19.188 --> 00:52:23.118
You're absolutely right. I don't know what I was thinking.

00:52:26.988 --> 00:52:28.098
Here you go.

00:52:37.668 --> 00:52:42.078
By designing stores where customers can experience the brand's story,

00:52:42.778 --> 00:52:47.148
we plan to reposition the brand to solidify its luxury image.

00:52:47.478 --> 00:52:49.978
Could you tell us a bit about the key design elements?

00:52:50.178 --> 00:52:53.788
As for the design details, our head designer at Taehan,

00:52:53.888 --> 00:52:55.818
Ms. Gong Ju Ah, will be explaining.

00:52:57.558 --> 00:53:01.598
Our FG premium line is characterized by its elegance and luxury,

00:53:01.658 --> 00:53:04.798
as well as a free-spirited beauty that truly stands out.

00:53:05.428 --> 00:53:06.798
The pattern is so intricate.

00:53:07.198 --> 00:53:09.498
Yes. And if you look here,

00:53:09.668 --> 00:53:14.208
this skirt is designed to sway like this with every movement.

00:53:14.838 --> 00:53:18.848
When you see it on, you'll notice it creates a very unique silhouette.

00:53:19.378 --> 00:53:24.318
I've worn it. It's not restrictive, so you feel very free, and yet...

00:53:28.688 --> 00:53:32.528
Great work today. I'm going to head home from here.

00:53:33.958 --> 00:53:35.858
Okay. See you, Mr. Yang.

00:53:45.708 --> 00:53:47.338
She's a tough one, Gong Ju Ah.

00:53:48.708 --> 00:53:50.038
I'm the only one who's a mess.

00:53:54.108 --> 00:53:55.518
Cheers!

00:53:57.018 --> 00:53:58.288
Look at you, Woo Jae. All grown up.

00:53:58.788 --> 00:54:00.588
Asking your old uncle out for a drink.

00:54:07.728 --> 00:54:09.928
What? Is that all you're having?

00:54:10.658 --> 00:54:12.328
I can totally carry you home tonight if you get drunk.

00:54:12.868 --> 00:54:14.338
I'll just wet my whistle.

00:54:15.798 --> 00:54:17.568
If I drink too much,

00:54:18.568 --> 00:54:20.068
there's no telling what I might do.

00:54:21.438 --> 00:54:24.348
Uncle, are you sure you'll be okay not moving away from everything?

00:54:24.748 --> 00:54:26.748
I hate the idea of the family moving because of me,

00:54:28.048 --> 00:54:30.178
and I can't bear to watch my brother go through a hard time.

00:54:30.748 --> 00:54:33.518
Excuse me, I'll have the beef ribs and a bottle of soju...

00:54:42.058 --> 00:54:43.958
On second thought, never mind.

00:54:59.578 --> 00:55:01.448
Uncle, what is it? Are you okay?

00:55:01.818 --> 00:55:03.518
- Hey, give me some water. - Yes.

00:55:08.588 --> 00:55:12.488
I have a feeling Dong Ik and his family aren't moving.

00:55:13.758 --> 00:55:15.098
I had a feeling.

00:55:15.958 --> 00:55:19.198
Mom, do you really have your heart set on moving?

00:55:20.398 --> 00:55:23.368
Honestly, I'm on the fence about it.

00:55:24.838 --> 00:55:27.008
I'm dying to move,

00:55:27.408 --> 00:55:28.838
but we both know our financial situation.

00:55:29.378 --> 00:55:31.478
And I'm worried about Seong Mi pushing herself too hard.

00:55:32.448 --> 00:55:34.208
You don't want to move at all, do you?

00:55:35.078 --> 00:55:37.788
It's not that I don't want to. It's that we can't.

00:55:38.148 --> 00:55:42.188
And frankly, I feel bad you're taking on so much.

00:55:42.588 --> 00:55:47.558
There are no other local clinics. What about the patients if we leave?

00:55:47.958 --> 00:55:49.228
So... Mom.

00:55:49.958 --> 00:55:54.838
Dae Han said he's fine with it, so should we just stick it out?

00:55:55.068 --> 00:55:56.898
- Mom? - Hold on...

00:55:57.338 --> 00:55:58.538
My goodness, Dae Han.

00:55:58.938 --> 00:56:00.468
- Oh, my. - Hey, what's wrong with you?

00:56:00.838 --> 00:56:03.108
- Sweetheart, what's wrong? - Gosh, it hurts.

00:56:03.208 --> 00:56:06.948
He said his side is hurting a lot. I doubt it's acute appendicitis.

00:56:07.008 --> 00:56:09.348
- Dad, hurry and take a look. - Okay. Lay him down first.

00:56:09.418 --> 00:56:10.948
- Okay. - Get the door.

00:56:14.818 --> 00:56:19.328
Hey, take a deep breath for me. Okay, one, two...

00:56:19.588 --> 00:56:24.428
- Okay, right here... - Ouch, it hurts! Stop pressing.

00:56:24.498 --> 00:56:26.928
Hey, shouldn't we take him to the ER?

00:56:27.298 --> 00:56:32.008
No fever or rebound tenderness. I think it's just acute indigestion.

00:56:32.368 --> 00:56:35.578
- He doesn't smell of alcohol. - He barely had anything to drink.

00:56:37.808 --> 00:56:38.808
Mom.

00:56:39.708 --> 00:56:40.848
Rub my tummy.

00:56:42.448 --> 00:56:43.478
Seriously?

00:56:46.188 --> 00:56:47.288
What brought this on all of a sudden?

00:56:48.358 --> 00:56:51.358
- Hey, what is it? What's going on? - What is it?

00:56:53.828 --> 00:56:55.198
The way I see it...

00:56:55.528 --> 00:56:58.298
I don't think this is physical. I think he's just heartbroken.

00:56:59.028 --> 00:57:00.028
What do you mean?

00:57:00.598 --> 00:57:02.698
We ran into Eun Bin's aunt at the restaurant.

00:57:02.968 --> 00:57:05.168
When he saw her, his chest tightened,

00:57:05.168 --> 00:57:06.368
and then the stomach pain started.

00:57:08.238 --> 00:57:11.578
So his psychological trauma is manifesting physically.

00:57:11.878 --> 00:57:13.908
So it's psychogenic abdominal pain.

00:57:14.478 --> 00:57:17.148
So the encounter with that person was the trigger, right?

00:57:17.348 --> 00:57:21.958
Yes. If it continues, it can manifest as an organ disease.

00:57:23.588 --> 00:57:26.728
And here he was, pretending like everything was fine.

00:57:31.268 --> 00:57:33.628
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

00:57:38.538 --> 00:57:39.968
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

00:57:47.978 --> 00:57:51.118
(Korean Medicine Doctor Yang Dong Ik)

00:57:51.218 --> 00:57:53.148
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

00:57:55.618 --> 00:57:56.618
What is it?

00:57:58.058 --> 00:58:00.758
Meet me at the playground at 7pm tonight.

00:58:01.498 --> 00:58:02.498
What for?

00:58:02.958 --> 00:58:04.728
We're deciding with a coin toss.

00:58:05.498 --> 00:58:06.498
Decide what?

00:58:08.738 --> 00:58:10.138
Who has to move.

00:58:10.898 --> 00:58:11.908
What?

00:58:13.738 --> 00:58:14.738
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

00:58:36.598 --> 00:58:37.598
Shoot!

00:58:38.268 --> 00:58:40.468
My goodness! Darn it...

00:58:41.028 --> 00:58:42.038
Again.

00:58:51.248 --> 00:58:52.548
Yes!

00:58:54.508 --> 00:58:55.648
Aren't you heading home?

00:58:57.378 --> 00:58:58.648
What are you doing?

00:58:59.118 --> 00:59:00.388
You can go on ahead, Dad.

00:59:01.258 --> 00:59:05.158
The greatest showdown in history is about to unfold tonight.

00:59:06.528 --> 00:59:07.558
What are you talking about?

00:59:07.958 --> 00:59:12.328
Our family's destiny rests on this single coin.

00:59:15.038 --> 00:59:16.038
Father...

00:59:28.118 --> 00:59:29.218
What the...

00:59:30.018 --> 00:59:31.918
This thing's still stuck?

00:59:35.188 --> 00:59:36.418
Hey.

00:59:37.118 --> 00:59:39.628
Gong Jeong Han of the Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic.

00:59:40.188 --> 00:59:42.258
Hey, Yang Dong Ik of the Sunny Clinic.

00:59:42.358 --> 00:59:46.068
Are you really going to keep skipping study hall?

00:59:46.168 --> 00:59:47.598
Gosh, whatever.

00:59:47.928 --> 00:59:50.298
It's just so annoying. The other kids keep teasing me.

00:59:50.638 --> 00:59:53.168
Who cares? Hey, even if you...

00:59:53.338 --> 00:59:56.338
wear red underwear, you're still number one in school.

00:59:56.408 --> 00:59:59.808
- They're long johns, not underwear! - Right. Whatever you say.

00:59:59.908 --> 01:00:00.908
Anyway...

01:00:01.848 --> 01:00:02.848
Onjeong Snack Bar?

01:00:02.948 --> 01:00:06.348
What, why? What about your mom's spicy pork?

01:00:06.418 --> 01:00:09.418
Hey, have you seen the new girl working at the snack bar?

01:00:11.428 --> 01:00:12.428
In that case...

01:00:13.388 --> 01:00:15.458
Let's flip a coin for it.

01:00:16.158 --> 01:00:18.168
- Deal. - You're so going down.

01:00:21.298 --> 01:00:22.298
You're dead meat.

01:00:23.498 --> 01:00:24.498
All right.

01:00:27.968 --> 01:00:32.008
Okay. One, two, three.

01:00:32.708 --> 01:00:35.948
Okay. Nice! Yes! Dear Lord, thank you!

01:00:36.018 --> 01:00:39.088
- I can do this. - Make him miss. Go wide.

01:00:39.148 --> 01:00:42.258
Dear Lord. Please! Come on!

01:00:44.258 --> 01:00:47.558
Yes!

01:00:48.328 --> 01:00:49.358
Gong Jeong Han.

01:00:54.098 --> 01:00:55.768
You're here.

01:00:56.638 --> 01:01:00.368
- No do-overs. - Of course. Don't you back out.

01:01:00.708 --> 01:01:02.908
- You throw first. - How are we doing this?

01:01:03.178 --> 01:01:05.848
Best of five? Or best of three?

01:01:05.908 --> 01:01:08.348
Real men don't do that. Let's just do sudden death.

01:01:08.648 --> 01:01:09.648
Fine.

01:01:12.888 --> 01:01:13.888
Oh, my.

01:01:14.418 --> 01:01:16.718
Hey, that rock is still there.

01:01:18.658 --> 01:01:19.658
I know, right?

01:01:19.958 --> 01:01:21.958
I brought chalk to draw the line and everything.

01:01:22.628 --> 01:01:23.628
So,

01:01:23.898 --> 01:01:27.868
- the rules are the same as always? - Sure.

01:01:28.698 --> 01:01:31.908
Closest to the rock wins.

01:01:33.168 --> 01:01:34.168
Okay.

01:01:36.338 --> 01:01:39.478
- Draw it straight. - I'm trying to pray here. Quiet.

01:01:45.248 --> 01:01:48.718
- You're something else, really. - Shut it. You'll jinx me.

01:01:56.728 --> 01:02:00.598
Yes! Did you see that? Did you see? It's crazy close.

01:02:01.128 --> 01:02:03.638
You're annoyingly good today. Darn it.

01:02:03.738 --> 01:02:05.938
- You nervous? - What the...

01:02:07.168 --> 01:02:09.178
- No way! Miss! - I can do this.

01:02:09.238 --> 01:02:12.448
- Fail! - I can do it. I can do it.

01:02:12.548 --> 01:02:14.308
- Dear Lord! - Let's go!

01:02:14.378 --> 01:02:16.078
- You will lose! - Let's go!

01:02:16.318 --> 01:02:17.478
Here I go!

01:02:23.288 --> 01:02:24.318
What the...

01:02:26.788 --> 01:02:29.128
Hey, are you kidding me? What is this?

01:02:29.428 --> 01:02:30.698
Hey, do-over.

01:02:31.968 --> 01:02:34.468
I lost. I'm off.

01:02:35.238 --> 01:02:37.538
- What? - I'll leave.

01:02:38.268 --> 01:02:39.268
We're moving.

01:02:47.078 --> 01:02:48.848
(Episodes 11 and 12 will air back-to-back...)

01:02:48.848 --> 01:02:50.618
(on Sunday, March 8 at 8pm.)

01:03:15.708 --> 01:03:18.248
(Recipe for Love)

01:03:18.308 --> 01:03:21.618
- Can we really afford to move? - Just trust me.

01:03:21.678 --> 01:03:24.348
We have to postpone the launch of your solo show.

01:03:25.018 --> 01:03:27.948
I heard you're having trouble moving because money's tight.

01:03:28.788 --> 01:03:29.988
The model for our premium line...

01:03:30.058 --> 01:03:33.128
Dr. Han Seong Mi? Pacu Nacho stopped her project.

01:03:33.888 --> 01:03:36.958
- What? - She would've been the ideal model.

01:03:37.028 --> 01:03:39.228
How could you let me down like this?

01:03:40.098 --> 01:03:43.098
I'm surprised you're the one who came to see the house.

01:03:43.868 --> 01:03:46.238
You should've kept your wife under control.

01:03:46.308 --> 01:03:49.538
- Hey, what did you say? - Seeing her made you sick?

01:03:49.638 --> 01:03:51.908
It's a stomachache. I'm getting an endoscopy tomorrow.

01:03:53.308 --> 01:03:55.448
Mom, this means we can't move.